.TH LOA-EXPORT-OBSIDIAN 1 "2026-03-23" "Library Of Alexandria" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
export obsidian \- Export library notes for an Obsidian vault
.SH SYNOPSIS
alexandria> export obsidian /path/to/your/vault
.SH DESCRIPTION
Exports your collection as markdown notes into:
.br
\fB<vault>/Alexandria/\fR
.br
Each managed note contains a protected generated block:
.br
\fB<!-- ALEXANDRIA:START --> ... <!-- ALEXANDRIA:END -->\fR
.br
During later syncs, only that block is replaced, so your own Analysis/Notes text stays intact.
.br
Generated notes use enforced sections: Metadata, Connections, Analysis, Notes.
.br
The export writes a Bases-first GUI (\fBAlexandria/Bases/*.base\fR), Dataview dashboards,
MOC pages (including Genres), saved searches, bookmarks page, smart analysis pages,
template files, a sync report, and a CSS snippet at \fB.obsidian/snippets/alexandria.css\fR.
.br
Obsidian settings are also updated for GUI usage:
\fB.obsidian/templates.json\fR, \fB.obsidian/bookmarks.json\fR, \fB.obsidian/workspace.json\fR,
and graph defaults for exploration.
.br
If legacy duplicate Alexandria roots are detected in the vault, sync/export
consolidates them to the canonical \fBAlexandria/\fR root.
.br
Tags matching genre names are excluded from Obsidian tag output to prevent overlap.
.br
The vault path is stored and reused by \fBobsidian sync\fR and \fBobsidian open\fR.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
alexandria> export obsidian ~/Documents/MyVault
.TP
alexandria> export obsidian /Users/me/Obsidian/MainVault
.SH SEE ALSO
loa(1), loa-export(1), loa-obsidian(1), loa-obsidian-sync(1), loa-obsidian-doctor(1), loa-obsidian-open(1)
